ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

Perceived Maternal Parenting Self-Efficacy (PMP S-E) Factor 1: Care Taking Procedures subscore
Notes: Sum of care taking items pmpse_caretaking1 through pmpse_caretaking4

ElementDescription: Perceived Maternal Parenting Self-Efficacy (PMP S-E) Factor 2: Evoking Behavior subscore
Notes: Sum of evoking behavior items pmpse__evoking1 through pmpse_evoking7

ElementDescription: Perceived Maternal Parenting Self-Efficacy (PMP S-E) Factor 3: Reading Behavior or Signaling subscore
Notes: Sum of reading behavior items pmpse_reading1 through pmpse_reading6

ElementDescription: Perceived Maternal Parenting Self-Efficacy (PMP S-E) Factor 4: Situational Beliefs
Notes: Sum of situational belief items pmpse_situational1 through pmpse_situational3

ElementDescription: Perceived Maternal Parenting Self-Efficacy (PMP S-E) Total Score
Notes: Higher scores indicate higher levels of maternal self-efficacy

ElementDescription: Age of the fetus (i.e., gestational age) in days
Type of gestational age used for fetal_age
Notes: 1 = Postovulatory gestational age, defined as days since the last ovulation, expected term of 266 days; 2 = Postmenstrual gestational age, days since the last menstrual period, expected term of 280 days

ElementDescription: Timepoint/visit label
Notes: e.g., Baseline, 6-Month Follow Up, Year 2; Morning, At Bedtime
